And they, they just, they weren't working anymore.

06:24.738 --> 06:26.200
Couldn't even roll on it.

06:26.220 --> 06:27.902
They wouldn't even spin one rotation.

06:31.706 --> 06:38.273
You ever had that experience where you do something not in the right season and it screws everything up.

06:40.335 --> 06:42.898
My daughter, Adley, she was made for the summer.

06:44.220 --> 06:45.722
She was made for summer.

06:47.043 --> 06:49.205
And she's got her best friend right across the street.

06:50.166 --> 06:53.330
And whenever her friend comes over, she gets so excited.

06:53.890 --> 07:03.423
I mean, so excited, because I don't know where you live, but in our neighborhood, it feels like everybody, everybody has an inflatable water park in their backyard.

07:05.626 --> 07:06.107
I looked it up.

07:06.167 --> 07:09.632
I mean, these things are like $800, and we don't.

07:10.874 --> 07:17.743
So Adley gets so excited, because when her friend comes over, she's going to the water park in her friend's backyard.

07:19.225 --> 07:22.610
And so she runs up, and she's like, Dad, Mom,

07:22.690 --> 07:23.251
Can I go play?

07:23.271 --> 07:23.811
Can I go play?

07:23.831 --> 07:24.412
Can I go play?

07:24.432 --> 07:25.012
Can I go play?

07:25.032 --> 07:25.913
Can I go play?

07:25.933 --> 07:35.964
She's so excited and as soon as we say yes, she forgets everything that she's doing and she starts running like dead sprint, but she's got to cross the street and so we've been trying to teach her.

07:36.464 --> 07:38.706
Hey, you were made for summer.

07:38.987 --> 07:41.970
This summer is gonna be awesome, but you need to slow down.

07:43.231 --> 07:43.511
Why?

07:44.472 --> 07:50.098
Because if she is so excited, caught up for the thing that she feels like she was made to do,

07:50.562 --> 07:53.667
She will forget to look both ways as she crosses the street.

07:54.108 --> 08:01.660
And you got to teach a hard lesson to a six-year-old saying, if you don't look both ways, there is a chance that you will get hit by a car.

08:02.281 --> 08:08.831
And is it an amazing that sometimes we run after the thing that we felt like we were made for?

08:09.432 --> 08:13.138
And it causes us sometimes to disobey what the Lord is telling us to do.

08:13.730 --> 08:30.726
It causes us to drop everything that we're doing and run after that thing, but the thing that we're running after, if we're not careful in following God's timing, knowing what season, like riding healies in the dead of winter through snow, it could kill us.

08:33.029 --> 08:42.898
We're talking about it's not about the fire and this grappling hook verse, delight yourself in the Lord and He'll give you the desires of your heart and culture

08:43.074 --> 08:47.238
What we live in today tells you delight yourself in your desires.

08:50.101 --> 08:51.342
And you'll get your desires.

08:52.383 --> 08:54.885
Trust in yourself and your own experience.

08:55.426 --> 08:56.407
Do what you want to do.

08:56.507 --> 08:57.468
Figure out your truth.

08:57.808 --> 08:58.589
Find yourself.

08:58.909 --> 08:59.430
Go get it.

08:59.630 --> 09:01.732
Delight yourself in your desires.

09:01.772 --> 09:03.193
But that's not what the Word of God says.

09:04.254 --> 09:06.036
Delight yourself in the Lord.

09:06.957 --> 09:09.860
And He will give you the desires of your heart.

09:11.341 --> 09:12.242
Culture says it's

09:12.322 --> 09:13.743
all about the fire.

09:15.065 --> 09:27.878
And if there's not a bonfire happening in your life, in whatever area, the workplace or your marriage or in parenting or the thing that you're pursuing or the big dream in your heart, if it's not happening, there's something wrong.

09:28.158 --> 09:29.239
There's something broken.

09:29.299 --> 09:30.320
There's something not right.

09:30.601 --> 09:33.424
And you should just give it up and quit or you should move forward.

09:33.844 --> 09:35.866
There's something wrong if there's not a fire.

09:36.146 --> 09:39.730
And I want to tell you today, there may not be anything wrong.

09:40.674 --> 09:45.802
as you delight yourself in the Lord and you wait patiently for Him.

09:46.663 --> 10:02.407
The Bible says that the meek, the calm, the content, those that have a conviction of moral living, biblical living, those that are quietly peaceful, they will inherit the earth.

10:02.948 --> 10:09.298
Culture says it's all about the fire, but the Bible says it's not about the fire, but we have a job to do.

10:10.018 --> 10:10.799
What is the fire?

10:11.981 --> 10:13.723
First of all, there's a spark of salvation.

10:14.665 --> 10:21.615
Spark of salvation, when you give your life to the Lord, you go from dead in your trespasses and alive in Christ.

10:21.975 --> 10:27.463
Ephesians chapter two says you were dead in your trespasses, but you've become alive in Christ.

10:27.904 --> 10:28.765
And we believe that.

10:29.186 --> 10:35.455
We believe that when we give our life to the Lord, it's like we are resurrected alive in Christ.

10:35.495 --> 10:37.458
The old is gone, the new has come.

10:37.538 --> 10:38.139
You're alive.

10:38.159 --> 10:39.100
There's a spark.

10:39.380 --> 10:41.883
When you give your life to Christ, there's a flame going.

10:42.144 --> 10:43.385
There's a fire going.

10:43.606 --> 10:45.248
It's something that's building up.

10:48.271 --> 10:51.215
It's our job, like we said, to tend to that fire.

10:51.896 --> 10:53.037
To tend to the fire.

10:53.398 --> 10:57.183
It's not about focusing on the big season, the big bonfire.

10:57.283 --> 10:58.344
It's about tending.

10:58.424 --> 11:00.647
It's about tending, and we'll get into it.

11:02.189 --> 11:06.354
Not just the spark of salvation, but the dreams that are in your heart.

11:07.074 --> 11:07.915
What is the fire?

11:09.997 --> 11:11.598
Let's build a fake fire over here.

11:13.620 --> 11:13.720
Cool?

11:13.740 --> 11:14.121
Right here.

11:15.642 --> 11:18.585
The fire is the dreams that God's placed in your heart.

11:19.386 --> 11:24.811
Think about right now, the greatest thing you could ever do for the kingdom.

11:25.732 --> 11:28.314
Thinking about how has God wired me?

11:28.354 --> 11:29.135
What has He created me?

11:29.335 --> 11:30.537
What are the passions that I have?

11:30.837 --> 11:32.078
How could I be used by God?

11:32.098 --> 11:36.242
Think about the greatest thing you could ever do for the kingdom.

11:36.674 --> 11:40.218
