You go on your honeymoon, you're like, this is awesome.

13:04.787 --> 13:07.050
Like cutting down trees left and right, throwing it on.

13:07.070 --> 13:07.971
It's like bonfire.

13:08.511 --> 13:10.533
Oh, marriage is awesome.

13:11.174 --> 13:18.101
Then you come home from the honeymoon and you find out like where the trees go.

13:18.121 --> 13:21.124
And that's not like, that's reality.

13:21.625 --> 13:23.046
That's reality.

13:23.066 --> 13:23.727
That's life.

13:24.287 --> 13:24.668
That's life.

13:25.008 --> 13:26.770
But what's crazy is

13:26.978 --> 13:30.403
The Bible teaches us to learn to love faithfulness.

13:30.583 --> 13:32.466
It says feed on his faithfulness.

13:32.766 --> 13:35.390
And you'll learn, you're gonna grow and love faithfulness.

13:35.450 --> 13:37.874
And so a lot of times in marriage, it's just coming home.

13:39.776 --> 13:40.638
And being faithful.

13:41.739 --> 13:42.861
And it's twig days.

13:43.582 --> 13:49.330
And so God will tell you, hey, honeymoon was awesome, but now you gotta take out the trash.

13:51.253 --> 13:52.455
